{"type":"message","id":"e2f6c623","parentId":"b0c145fe","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:52:58.160Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ymev3jkz31j2_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 035215\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, compression-causal duality\r\n- The next action is clearly defined: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action from Phase 1 Advancement is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should implement the TIC experiment. Let me look at what's in the logs directory and create a classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what the pulse logs look like, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step to advance Phase 1. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant structure across the last 20 pulse logs, then measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant or variant, and measures prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Input:** Last 20 pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`)\r\n- **Classifier:** Rule-based + LLM-assisted invariant/variant detection\r\n- **Metrics:**\r\n  - Classification accuracy: % of content correctly labeled invariant/variant\r\n  - Prediction accuracy: % of next-pulse content predicted from invariants\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Classification: >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- Prediction: >60% next-pulse content match\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport glob\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\ndef get_recent_pulses(n=20):\r\n    logs = sorted(glob.glob(\"logs/pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    return logs[-n:]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\n```python\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features that indicate invariance vs variance.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"has_goal_update\": \"Goals:\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_mutation\": \"MUTATION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_observation\": \"OBSERVATION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_action\": \"ACTION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"file_references\": extract_file_paths(pulse_content),\r\n        \"code_blocks\": pulse_content.count(\"```\"),\r\n        \"question_marks\": pulse_content.count(\"?\"),\r\n        \"new_concepts\": count_concept_definitions(pulse_content),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Invariant Detection\r\n```python\r\nINVARIANTS = [\r\n    \"Goals:\", \"PENDING ACTIONS\", \"Phase\", \"##\",\r\n    \"MUTATION\", \"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\",\r\n    \"###\", \"file:\", \"```\"\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANCE_MARKERS = [\r\n    \"Last updated:\", \"This Session\", \"Derived\",\r\n    \"2026-\", \"2025-\", \"timestamp\"\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(text_segment):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify text as invariant (stable structure) or variant (content).\"\"\"\r\n    inv_score = sum(1 for m in INVARIANTS if m in text_segment)\r\n    var_score = sum(1 for m in VARIANCE_MARKERS if m in text_segment)\r\n    return \"invariant\" if inv_score > var_score else \"variant\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Prediction Test\r\n```python\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_set, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Use invariant structure to predict next pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    predicted = []\r\n    for inv in invariant_set:\r\n        if inv in current_pulse:\r\n            predicted.append(inv)\r\n    return predicted\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Output\r\n- Classification accuracy percentage\r\n- Prediction match percentage\r\n- List of discovered invariants\r\n- Next-pulse prediction vs actual comparison\r\n\r\n## Status: PENDING IMPLEMENTATION\r\nfile: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:52:39"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":505,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 035215\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, compression-causal duality\r\n- The next action is clearly defined: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action from Phase 1 Advancement is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should implement the TIC experiment. Let me look at what's in the logs directory and create a classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what the pulse logs look like, then implement the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step to advance Phase 1. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant structure across the last 20 pulse logs, then measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC experiment script that reads pulse logs, classifies content as invariant or variant, and measures prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Input:** Last 20 pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`)\r\n- **Classifier:** Rule-based + LLM-assisted invariant/variant detection\r\n- **Metrics:**\r\n  - Classification accuracy: % of content correctly labeled invariant/variant\r\n  - Prediction accuracy: % of next-pulse content predicted from invariants\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Classification: >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- Prediction: >60% next-pulse content match\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```python\r\nimport os\r\nimport glob\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\ndef get_recent_pulses(n=20):\r\n    logs = sorted(glob.glob(\"logs/pulse_*.md\"))\r\n    return logs[-n:]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\n```python\r\ndef extract_features(pulse_content):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features that indicate invariance vs variance.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"has_goal_update\": \"Goals:\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_mutation\": \"MUTATION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_observation\": \"OBSERVATION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"has_action\": \"ACTION\" in pulse_content,\r\n        \"file_references\": extract_file_paths(pulse_content),\r\n        \"code_blocks\": pulse_content.count(\"```\"),\r\n        \"question_marks\": pulse_content.count(\"?\"),\r\n        \"new_concepts\": count_concept_definitions(pulse_content),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Invariant Detection\r\n```python\r\nINVARIANTS = [\r\n    \"Goals:\", \"PENDING ACTIONS\", \"Phase\", \"##\",\r\n    \"MUTATION\", \"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\",\r\n    \"###\", \"file:\", \"```\"\r\n]\r\n\r\nVARIANCE_MARKERS = [\r\n    \"Last updated:\", \"This Session\", \"Derived\",\r\n    \"2026-\", \"2025-\", \"timestamp\"\r\n]\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(text_segment):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify text as invariant (stable structure) or variant (content).\"\"\"\r\n    inv_score = sum(1 for m in INVARIANTS if m in text_segment)\r\n    var_score = sum(1 for m in VARIANCE_MARKERS if m in text_segment)\r\n    return \"invariant\" if inv_score > var_score else \"variant\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Prediction Test\r\n```python\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_set, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Use invariant structure to predict next pulse content.\"\"\"\r\n    predicted = []\r\n    for inv in invariant_set:\r\n        if inv in current_pulse:\r\n            predicted.append(inv)\r\n    return predicted\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Output\r\n- Classification accuracy percentage\r\n- Prediction match percentage\r\n- List of discovered invariants\r\n- Next-pulse prediction vs actual comparison\r\n\r\n## Status: PENDING IMPLEMENTATION\r\nfile: experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n`\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:52:39","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338778158}}
